title.narrative: NUTRITION NORTH SYRIA

description.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical Nutrition needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP., which contributes to Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.

title.narrative: Syria's conflict-affected population have their critical Nutrition needs met, in line with the HRP and as part of the UNICEF JOP.

description.narrative: UNICEF and partners reached more than 1.7 million mothers, and children under five years old in North West Syria (NWS) in 2021. Nutrition services reached mothers and children at high-risk areas in IDP camps and hard to reach areas in NWS, using both fixed primary health care services as well as ambulatory services including supporting more than 173 rapid response teams (RRTs) providing integrated nutrition services. Nutrition services were utilized as entry points to disseminate Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE) messages on COVID-19 and nutrition services implemented following UNICEF global guidance | Status:Met | As-of Date:01/02/2022
